title: Teen found dead in motel over weekend identified - New Hampshire news
text:
ROCHESTER, N.H. (AP) â€” New Hampshire police have identified the 17-year-old girl whose body was found in a Rochester motel room over the weekend.
Evangelique Tarmey of Rochester was found at the Riviera Hotel early Saturday. Her mother and a male companion also were there.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Police said an autopsy was conducted on Saturday afternoon and the cause of death will not be determined until toxicology results are returned.
The Rochester Police Department continues to investigate this case and says it is being treated as a possible drug overdose.
Tarmey was a student at Spaulding High School.
